Task
Is the result of dividing two numbers finite?
Write a function checkingForFinite that takes two numbers a and b as arguments, dividing a by b, and checking the result of the division (quotient) by finitude. The function must return true if the result is a finite number, and false otherwise.
Examples:
• the checkingForFinite (4, 2) function must return true;
• the checkingForFinite (3, 0) function must return false;
• the checkingForFinite (-1, 0) function must return false.

Solution
function checkingForFinite (a, b) {
return Number.isFinite (a / b);
}
